## 6 Experiments

We compare Causal CPC with SOTA baselines: MSMs [64], RMSN [41], CRN [7], G-Net [39], and CT [48]. All models are fine-tuned via a grid search over hyperparameters, including architecture and optimizers. Model selection is based on mean squared error (MSE) on factual outcomes from a validation set, and the same criterion is used for early stopping. Further details on hyperparameters and training procedures are provided in Appendices J and D.

### Experiments with Synthetic Data

Tumor GrowthWe use the PharmacoKinetic-PharmacoDynamic (PK-PD) model [24] to simulate responses of non-small cell lung cancer patients, following previous works [41; 7; 48]. We evaluate our approach on simulated counterfactual trajectories, varying the confounding level via the parameter \(\gamma\) (Appendix E.1). Unlike [48], who used larger datasets (10,000 for training, 1,000 for testing), we use a smaller, more challenging dataset (1,000 for training, 500 for testing) to reflect real-world data limitations. For long-horizon forecasting, we set the prediction horizon to 10 and evaluate two training sequence lengths: 60 and 40, with covariates of dimension 4.

